[sigh] All of his duties
        have fallen to me.

42
00:01:44,872 --> 00:01:48,474
On the positive side,
this is a slow day.

43
00:01:48,476 --> 00:01:49,575
Slow day?!

44
00:01:49,577 --> 00:01:51,276
Well, leisurely.

45
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:53,278
Wait till you see
what's lined up for tomorrow.

46
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,546
[groans]

47
00:01:54,548 --> 00:01:56,782
[Armando] Oh, Princess,
    you know what happens

48
00:01:56,784 --> 00:01:58,750
when your emotions
       get too strong.

49
00:01:58,752 --> 00:02:00,752
Your dress lights up and--

50
00:02:00,754 --> 00:02:01,820
Look out!

51
00:02:01,822 --> 00:02:03,222
Here comes the feely-magic!

52
00:02:03,224 --> 00:02:06,658
Oh! My precious pearls!

53
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,894
Now what am I going to clutch?

54
00:02:08,896 --> 00:02:10,696
[deep breath]

55
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:14,733
-[both whimpering]
       -Sorry about that.

56
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:17,069
At least she stayed
          in her frame. [laughs]

57
00:02:17,071 --> 00:02:18,170
This time.

58
00:02:18,172 --> 00:02:19,738
There you are,<i> mijita!</i>

59
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:23,108
Are you ready for
  our weekly game of<i> Conquian?</i>

60
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:25,744
Sorry,<i> abuela.</i>
     I'm swamped with work.

61
00:02:25,746 --> 00:02:28,413
[sigh] No matter
               how busy you are,

62
00:02:28,415 --> 00:02:31,416
you should always
          make time for<i> familia.</i>

63
00:02:32,585 --> 00:02:35,120
Armando, please
            change the schedule.

64
00:02:35,122 --> 00:02:37,689
-Move<i> Conquian</i> to Thursday.
  -[gasp]

65
00:02:37,691 --> 00:02:40,125
Bumping to Thursday.

66
00:02:40,127 --> 00:02:42,694
I've been bumped?

67
00:02:42,696 --> 00:02:44,663
Hmm mmm...

68
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:45,764
[gasp]

69
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:49,601
Introducing
              the Hydro-Gondola!

70
00:02:52,539 --> 00:02:54,840
By using Avalor's waterfalls,

71
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,508
we can power
a transportation system

72
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,510
that will help everyone
get around the city.

73
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,712
No more traffic.

74
00:03:00,714 --> 00:03:01,713
Huh!

75
00:03:01,715 --> 00:03:04,183
You're a genius, Isa.

76
00:03:04,185 --> 00:03:06,218
Well, I guess I didn't need
     to ask King Joaquín

77
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:08,854
to come show us how he made
     Cariza's gondola system.

78
00:03:08,856 --> 00:03:10,455
[gasp]

79
00:03:10,457 --> 00:03:11,690
[creaking]

80
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:13,225
[Flo] Aah!

81
00:03:13,227 --> 00:03:15,827
But, since he's already
         on his way,

82
00:03:15,829 --> 00:03:18,330
it would be rude
          to cancel last minute.

83
00:03:18,332 --> 00:03:19,531
Ohhhh!

84
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:20,632
I need to reinforce the grips

85
00:03:20,634 --> 00:03:22,634
and recalculate
       the counterweight.

86
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:25,037
Princess Elena,
it's time for your next meeting.

87
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:27,172
Oh, uh, sorry, Armando,

88
00:03:27,174 --> 00:03:29,541
but I have to help Isa
     weigh the counters.

89
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:30,676
The counterweight?

90
00:03:30,678 --> 00:03:31,977
That's what I said.

91
00:03:31,979 --> 00:03:33,579
I better
      clear your schedule.

92
00:03:33,581 --> 00:03:35,147
[Flo] I'll do it!

93
00:03:35,149 --> 00:03:36,715
All clear!

94
00:03:45,491 --> 00:03:47,926
Mmm,<i> delicioso.</i>

95
00:03:47,928 --> 00:03:52,030
So, Elena, Isabel,
              how was your day?

96
00:03:52,032 --> 00:03:54,166
The main support struts
need to be constructed

97
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,001
someplace
with optimum stability.

98
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:58,103
Well, let's look
                at our options.

99
00:03:58,105 --> 00:04:01,673
Oh, we had a great day,
    <i> abuela.</i>

100
00:04:01,675 --> 00:04:04,409
Thank you so much
      for asking,<i> abuela.</i>

101
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:05,777
Farsight!

102
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:09,514
What about
    this clearing by the bridge?

103
00:04:09,516 --> 00:04:11,617
Hmm. That would take
maximum advantage--

104
00:04:11,619 --> 00:04:12,684
Turn that thing off!

105
00:04:12,686 --> 00:04:13,719
-Aah!
             -Oh!

106
00:04:13,721 --> 00:04:15,721
No scepter
            at the dinner table!

107
00:04:15,723 --> 00:04:17,456
This is family time.

108
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,890
Sorry,<i> abuela.</i>

109
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:20,259
When I was a girl,

110
00:04:20,261 --> 00:04:22,728
<i> familia</i>
             always came first.

111
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:26,098
We all worked and played
        and ate together.

112
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:29,635
We weren't royal,
       but we were rich in love.

113
00:04:29,637 --> 00:04:33,972
My<i> abuelos</i> were the finest
     chocolate-makers in Avalor.

114
00:04:33,974 --> 00:04:36,642
Their shop was called
          <i> La Vida Dulce.</i>

115
00:04:36,644 --> 00:04:39,478
People would travel
           from around the world
           just to get a taste.

116
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,313
[whispering]
       What I was saying,

117
00:04:41,315 --> 00:04:43,081
the clearing by the bridge
      would be the best place

118
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,249
to put the Hydro-Gondola.

119
00:04:44,251 --> 00:04:46,218
[clearing throat]

120
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:49,588
You were saying...
        about the, uh, people...

121
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:53,825
Wouldn't it be nice
 if we had something like that?

122
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:56,795
Something we could do
        together, just us girls?

123
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:57,996
Uh...

124
00:04:57,998 --> 00:05:00,432
Why not reopen<i> La Vida Dulce?</i>

125
00:05:00,434 --> 00:05:02,734
It is just sitting there
    all closed up.

126
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:04,970
[gasp] You are right,
     <i> mi amor!</i>

127
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:06,571
We should do it.

128
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:09,508
Ooooh, exciting!
     What do you two think?

129
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:11,510
[whispering] Yeah,
the optimal proximity--

130
00:05:11,512 --> 00:05:13,111
<i> -Mijitas!</i>
           -[gasp]

131
00:05:13,113 --> 00:05:15,280
Right! Armando,
                 can we fit in

132
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,416
what<i> abuela</i> said
                for tomorrow?

133
00:05:17,418 --> 00:05:19,785
I'm afraid tomorrow
     is completely booked.

134
00:05:19,787 --> 00:05:21,486
Check again!

135
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,755
Eh heh! Look at that.

136
00:05:23,757 --> 00:05:25,424
We just had a cancellation.

137
00:05:25,426 --> 00:05:27,492
Perfect, then it's settled.

138
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:30,495
<i> La Vida Dulce</i>
     is open for business!

139
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:32,664
Yay! [laughs]

140
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,199
[whispering]
           What's<i> La Vida Dulce?</i>

141
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:35,500
[whispering] No idea.

142
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:53,719
Now, the secret
          to delicious chocolate
          is in the mixing.

143
00:05:53,721 --> 00:05:56,321
Turn and fold gently.

144
00:05:56,323 --> 00:06:00,158
You've been turning
and folding gently
for a while now.

145
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:03,628
How long until we're
sitting and eating happily?

146
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,996
Flo!

147
00:06:04,998 --> 00:06:07,065
Oh, like I was
       the only one thinking it.

148
00:06:07,067 --> 00:06:09,568
It takes time
      to do things right.

149
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:11,803
We want people to taste
    the care and love

150
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:14,539
that went into
     making the chocolate.

151
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,175
That's the<i> La Vida Dulce</i> way.

152
00:06:17,177 --> 00:06:18,643
I remember spending all day

153
00:06:18,645 --> 00:06:21,380
making chocolate
        with<i> mi familia.</i>

154
00:06:21,382 --> 00:06:24,850
Then, after closing time,
  we would go to Castillo Park

155
00:06:24,852 --> 00:06:27,652
and feed the leftover nuts
   to the squirrels.

156
00:06:27,654 --> 00:06:29,654
Well, don't you worry.

157
00:06:29,656 --> 00:06:32,190
I'll take care
of any leftover anything.

158
00:06:32,192 --> 00:06:33,992
[chuckles]

159
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:35,394
Well, now we place the mold

160
00:06:35,396 --> 00:06:37,662
in the cold closet
       until it hardens.

161
00:06:38,731 --> 00:06:40,399
What are we making next?

162
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:42,367
Honey hazelnut clusters.

163
00:06:42,369 --> 00:06:44,569
[gasp] Ay, no!

164
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:46,438
