237
00:09:46,053 --> 00:09:48,353
And we will. Later.

238
00:09:48,355 --> 00:09:50,755
[sigh]

239
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:55,460
Isa, why don't you
              stay here?

240
00:09:55,462 --> 00:09:57,529
But I designed
the Hydro-Gondola.

241
00:09:57,531 --> 00:10:01,132
I know, but I think<i> abuela</i>
     could use some company.

242
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:03,101
[hazelnuts clinking
      in bowl]

243
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:05,604
[sigh] Okay. Here.

244
00:10:05,606 --> 00:10:07,806
[clattering]

245
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:11,309
Ah, a gift for the Carizans.
    Good thinking, Flo.

246
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:14,079
Actually, I was thinking
about a snack for me,

247
00:10:14,081 --> 00:10:17,549
but, yeah, sure,
just give 'em away. Swell.

248
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:22,654
Hello.

249
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:25,690
And goodbye.

250
00:10:27,059 --> 00:10:28,259
Ooh! Whoo!

251
00:10:28,261 --> 00:10:30,295
Wowie-wow!

252
00:10:30,297 --> 00:10:31,496
Hey! Ow!

253
00:10:31,498 --> 00:10:32,597
Who put that wall there?

254
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:34,299
And there? And there?

255
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,167
-[thuds and clanks]
     -And there? And there?

256
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,305
Now attach
              the counterweight
              to the bull wheel.

257
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:42,574
[Elena]
     Wow. Very impressive.

258
00:10:42,576 --> 00:10:47,846
Elena! I, uh...
          am making a few tweaks
          to your Hydro-Gondola.

259
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:49,681
I hope you don't mind.

260
00:10:49,683 --> 00:10:50,915
Not at all.

261
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:52,917
We just have
                a few questions.

262
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:54,653
Yes, we do.

263
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,855
What is the...

264
00:10:56,857 --> 00:11:02,627
elevational apex of--
 of your proposed aerial track?

265
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:06,264
Oh. I, uh...
Let me just check.

266
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:10,635
423 feet
                above sea level.

267
00:11:10,637 --> 00:11:12,937
Yup.
That sounds about right.

268
00:11:12,939 --> 00:11:19,010
And, uh,
what is the estimated
longitudinal, uh...

269
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:20,712
[whispers]
                      Span.

270
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:23,515
Span-- ha ha, yes--
that you hope to achieve?

271
00:11:23,517 --> 00:11:25,717
That's um... uh...

272
00:11:25,719 --> 00:11:27,552
Um...

273
00:11:27,554 --> 00:11:30,221
I calculate better in nature.

274
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:35,060
-[Caterina gasps]
   -[loud clanks and crashes]

275
00:11:35,062 --> 00:11:36,494
Elena, what's happening?!

276
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:39,698
-Oh, um, I gotta go!
      -But, Elena!

277
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:41,199
Here! It's a welcome gift!

278
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:43,468
Ooh! Avaloran chocolate.

279
00:11:51,577 --> 00:11:52,811
[barking]

280
00:11:56,082 --> 00:11:57,182
-Ooh!
           -Hey! Oh.

281
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:58,349
-Excuse me.
          -Sorry.

282
00:11:58,351 --> 00:12:00,652
[horse whinnies]

283
00:12:00,654 --> 00:12:04,389
<i> Gracias,</i>
    enjoy your chocolates.

284
00:12:04,391 --> 00:12:06,057
Elena, you're back!

285
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:08,660
Uh, actually, I just came
     to borrow Isabel for a bit.

286
00:12:08,662 --> 00:12:10,595
-But I thought--
        -I know, I know,

287
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:12,430
but I'm
            in way over my head.

288
00:12:12,432 --> 00:12:14,733
I need Isa's help
    with all this gondola stuff,

289
00:12:14,735 --> 00:12:17,435
and I'm barely keeping it
       together as it is.

290
00:12:17,437 --> 00:12:20,238
[sigh]
For the good of the kingdom.

291
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:24,843
[sigh]

292
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:28,313
Whoa!

293
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,585
[high-pitched voice]
   Hi, Isabel, you're gonna love
   our gondola's speed regulator

294
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:36,221
when you see it in action.
   It's so fast!

295
00:12:36,223 --> 00:12:38,590
Uh... why are you
       talking like that?

296
00:12:38,592 --> 00:12:40,959
[high-pitched voice] We also
    rigged up an entire track
    for a demonstration!

297
00:12:40,961 --> 00:12:42,160
Let's show 'em!

298
00:12:49,201 --> 00:12:50,602
[Caterina]
      Whoo-hoo! [laughing]

299
00:12:50,604 --> 00:12:52,937
Whoa-ho! Yes!

300
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:54,072
Ha ha ha!

301
00:12:54,074 --> 00:12:56,374
[both cheering]

302
00:12:56,376 --> 00:12:58,476
[gasp] No, stop!

303
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,453
[parts clanking]

304
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:10,355
Aaaah!

305
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:17,328
Oh! Okay.

306
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,663
Calm down, Elena.

307
00:13:18,665 --> 00:13:19,798
[deep breath]

308
00:13:22,902 --> 00:13:24,536
[cable creaking]

309
00:13:26,772 --> 00:13:30,742
Baby Jaquins, baby Jaquins,
baby Jaquins.

310
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:34,078
Baby Jaquins. [sigh]

311
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,580
[tap tap]

312
00:13:35,582 --> 00:13:36,514
-Ohh!
             -Whew!

313
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,484
[high-pitched voice]
 We need to add a support strut

314
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:40,852
and recalibrate
       the line tension,

315
00:13:40,854 --> 00:13:42,520
but don't worry, we're on it!

316
00:13:42,522 --> 00:13:44,589
[high-pitched voice]
            Uh, what she said.

317
00:13:44,591 --> 00:13:47,926
Wait! You don't need
 to build the whole thing now!

318
00:13:47,928 --> 00:13:48,993
Wait!

319
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:51,863
Zuzo!

320
00:13:51,865 --> 00:13:53,131
Hiya, Princess.

321
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,699
I don't know
                what's going on!

322
00:13:54,701 --> 00:13:56,634
I got nervous,
     and my New Magic kicked in,

323
00:13:56,636 --> 00:13:58,770
but when I calmed down,
         the statues re-statued
         themselves,

324
00:13:58,772 --> 00:14:00,672
but Joaquín and Cat
         are still acting weird.

325
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:01,706
[Isabel] Wait!

326
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:03,875
Slow down!

327
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:07,011
Well, that<i> is</i> peculiar.

328
00:14:09,648 --> 00:14:11,182
What's this?

329
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:13,318
Oh, I made them
           chocolates as a gift.

330
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,954
Huh, mmm... Uh-huh.

331
00:14:15,956 --> 00:14:18,790
And how were you feeling
when you made the chocolates?

332
00:14:18,792 --> 00:14:20,692
In a hurry
               to get back here.

333
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:21,826
Aha!

334
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:23,328
If you were feeling
really frantic

335
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,529
while you were baking,

336
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:25,897
it might've triggered
           your magic,

337
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,565
which got
            into the chocolates,

338
00:14:27,567 --> 00:14:28,800
and then got into them.

339
00:14:28,802 --> 00:14:30,568
Cat, stop!

340
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:32,470
Uh-oh.
I need to stop<i> abuela</i>

341
00:14:32,472 --> 00:14:34,906
from selling
any more chocolates!

342
00:14:34,908 --> 00:14:36,107
You're welcome.

343
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,643
Wait for me!

344
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:44,515
Whoo!

345
00:14:44,517 --> 00:14:46,384
Closed!

346
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:48,686
Our chocolates can't cause
      any more problems now.

347
00:14:48,688 --> 00:14:49,988
<i> Abuela?</i>

348
00:14:51,991 --> 00:14:53,291
<i> Abuela?</i>

349
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:56,194
Hmm. Where'd she go?

350
00:14:56,196 --> 00:14:58,596
And why is everything
     packed up?

351
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:07,839
Because there's
       no<i> familia</i> chocolate shop

352
00:15:07,841 --> 00:15:09,140
without the<i> familia.</i>

353
00:15:12,511 --> 00:15:14,846
The only reason
      she reopened<i> La Vida Dulce</i>

354
00:15:14,848 --> 00:15:16,547
was to spend time with us.

355
00:15:16,549 --> 00:15:19,017
And we left her all alone.

356
00:15:19,019 --> 00:15:22,086
[sniffles]
We hurt her feelings.

357
00:15:22,088 --> 00:15:25,123
No, this is all on me, Isa.

358
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:28,226
I've had so much to do,
    I forgot the one thing

359
00:15:28,228 --> 00:15:31,529
that matters more than
     all the royal business
     in the world.

360
00:15:31,531 --> 00:15:33,097
-We have to find her.
     -[crunch]

361
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,201
Huh, hazelnuts.

362
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:39,604
[gasp] I think I have
         an idea where she went!

363
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:44,509
[chittering]

364
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,114
Mind if we join you?

365
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:53,718
Are you sure
          you can squeeze me in?

366
00:16:03,495 --> 00:16:05,229
When I was a little girl,

367
00:16:05,231 --> 00:16:07,966
all we had was
      the chocolate shop.

368
00:16:07,968 --> 00:16:09,968
So there was nowhere else
   to be but together.

369
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:14,405
But you have
       a kingdom to run,<i> mijita.</i>

370
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:16,541
Even more so
              with Esteban gone.

371
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:20,078
After all
   that's happened with him,

372
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,647
the shop was my way
    of keeping us together.

373
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:26,484
But I was foolish to try
    and relive the old days.

374
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:29,854
I just don't want to lose
   what's left of my<i> familia.</i>

375
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:34,425
You'll never lose us,
<i>abuela.</i>

376
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,594
And I was the one
who was foolish

377
00:16:36,596 --> 00:16:41,099
for not making
more time for you
and Isa and<i> abuelo.</i>

378
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,968
Nothing is more important
than<i> familia.</i>

379
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:45,503
Especially now.

380
00:16:46,872 --> 00:16:48,606
I love you,<i> abuela.</i>

381
00:16:48,608 --> 00:16:50,174
Me, too.

382
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:54,345
Ay, with this much sweetness,
 who needs chocolate?

383
00:16:54,347 --> 00:16:55,947
[gasp] The chocolate.

384
00:16:55,949 --> 00:16:58,116
Um,<i> abuela...</i>
[sheepish chuckle]

385
00:16:58,118 --> 00:16:59,851
There may have been
      something wrong

386
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:02,620
with the batch Isa and I made.

387
00:17:02,622 --> 00:17:05,723
Well, I'm not surprised,
   the way you were rushing.

388
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:09,160
No, I mean really wrong.

389
00:17:09,162 --> 00:17:10,628
I was in such a hurry,

390
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:12,630
my New Magic got
      into the chocolates.

391
00:17:12,632 --> 00:17:14,499
And now everyone
                who ate them

392
00:17:14,501 --> 00:17:16,801
is running
       around Avalor super-fast.

393
00:17:16,803 --> 00:17:19,704
And we have no idea
   how to fix it. [chuckles]

394
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:25,076
Well, maybe if you make
   a new batch the right way,

395
00:17:25,078 --> 00:17:27,512
slowly and calmly,

396
00:17:27,514 --> 00:17:29,647
your magic
     will create chocolates

397
00:17:29,649 --> 00:17:31,582
that return them to normal.

398
00:17:31,584 --> 00:17:35,420
That sounds
  like it could actually work.

399
00:17:35,422 --> 00:17:37,588
Your<i> abuelita</i>
      has some good ideas

400
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:40,024
if you take the time to listen.

401
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:41,526
[chittering]

402
00:17:41,528 --> 00:17:43,661
They're all yours,<i> pequeños.</i>

403
00:17:43,663 --> 00:17:45,997
We've got some baking to do!

404
00:17:48,534 --> 00:17:51,669
My<i> abuela</i> was a wizard
     in the kitchen.

405
00:17:51,671 --> 00:17:54,739
The whisk was her<i> tamborita,</i>
 this was her spell.

406
00:17:54,741 --> 00:17:57,708
[upbeat music]

407
00:17:57,710 --> 00:18:01,245
<i> ♪ Chocolate, oh so sweet ♪</i>

408
00:18:02,881 --> 00:18:06,651
<i> ♪ Chocolate, what a treat ♪</i>

409
00:18:08,454 --> 00:18:10,888
<i> ♪ Sugar</i>
  <i> with some powdered cocoa ♪</i>

410
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:13,624
<i> ♪ Piece by piece,</i> poco a poco ♪

411
00:18:13,626 --> 00:18:16,527
<i> ♪ Mix it, stir it,</i> fabuloso ♪

412
00:18:16,529 --> 00:18:19,530
<i> ♪ Bake it, cool it,</i>
      qué sabroso ♪

413
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:25,002
<i> ♪ Chocolate, oh so sweet ♪</i>

414
00:18:27,039 --> 00:18:29,474
<i> ♪ Chocolate, what a treat ♪</i>

415
00:18:29,476 --> 00:18:30,475
[giggles]

416
00:18:31,543 --> 00:18:33,077
Look!

417
00:18:33,079 --> 00:18:35,813
Let's hope it's
    the right kind of magic.

418
00:18:35,815 --> 00:18:37,715
We'll have to wait
              until they cool.

419
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:42,386
[gasp] They're ready.

420
00:18:42,388 --> 00:18:43,488
[Flo] Oh! Oh!

421
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:46,557
What is it
     with all these walls?!

422
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:48,392
Aah aah! Ooh!

423
00:18:48,394 --> 00:18:50,495
Flo must've eaten
             the chocolate, too!

424
00:18:50,497 --> 00:18:51,762
Here, eat this.

425
00:18:51,764 --> 00:18:53,097
What?! More chocolate?!

426
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:54,332
Happy to!

427
00:18:54,334 --> 00:18:56,501
[gulping]

428
00:18:56,503 --> 00:19:00,304
Whew! Maybe I'll take
a break from chocolates
for a little while.

429
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:01,839
Maybe...

430
00:19:01,841 --> 00:19:04,575
Looks like it's
        the right kind of magic.

431
00:19:04,577 --> 00:19:07,678
Now we just have to find
everyone else who ate them.

432
00:19:09,615 --> 00:19:11,182
Come and get 'em!

433
00:19:11,184 --> 00:19:13,751
Free<i> La Vida Dulce</i> chocolates!

434
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,323
Oh! Thanks!

435
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:21,425
Ah, feels so good
               to stop running.

436
00:19:21,427 --> 00:19:22,493
Doesn't it?

437
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:24,028
Maybe you can help me
pass out the rest

438
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,430
to anyone
who's rushing around, too.

439
00:19:26,432 --> 00:19:28,032
Sure thing.

440
00:19:28,034 --> 00:19:31,102
Free chocolates!
Free-- Oh!

441
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:37,675
King Joaquín and Cat
            are this way!

442
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:39,944
Maybe you two should
    give them the chocolate.

443
00:19:39,946 --> 00:19:41,546
What? Why?

444
00:19:41,548 --> 00:19:43,447
I can't tell them
     why this all happened.

445
00:19:43,449 --> 00:19:44,715
It's too embarrassing.

446
00:19:44,717 --> 00:19:46,184
How so?

447
00:19:46,186 --> 00:19:48,019
What am I supposed to say,

448
00:19:48,021 --> 00:19:50,788
that I have a mysterious power
that gets out of hand

449
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,890
when I can't control
my emotions?

450
00:19:52,892 --> 00:19:54,625
I'm the crown princess.

451
00:19:54,627 --> 00:19:56,360
I always need to be
      in control.

452
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:58,396
Or at least people
need to think that.

453
00:19:58,398 --> 00:20:02,333
<i> Mijita,</i>
             no one is perfect,

454
00:20:02,335 --> 00:20:03,901
not even royalty.

455
00:20:03,903 --> 00:20:06,404
King Joaquín
                will understand.

456
00:20:09,174 --> 00:20:10,575
Hey, everyone!

457
00:20:10,577 --> 00:20:12,677
Who wants
some more Avaloran chocolate?

458
00:20:12,679 --> 00:20:13,878
Yes, please!

459
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:18,349
[normal voice] Ohh!

460
00:20:18,351 --> 00:20:20,651
I don't understand
   why I was rushing around.

461
00:20:20,653 --> 00:20:22,386
I do.

462
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:24,922
Joaquín,
  I have a confession to make.

463
00:20:24,924 --> 00:20:27,458
The reason you were
     in such a hurry was...

464
00:20:29,194 --> 00:20:33,164
my magic got into
   the chocolate I gave you.

465
00:20:34,399 --> 00:20:36,000
A little while back,

466
00:20:36,002 --> 00:20:38,336
I fell into a well
      of magical crystals,

467
00:20:38,338 --> 00:20:41,405
and it gave me,
      uh, unusual powers.

468
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:42,440
[chuckles]

469
00:20:42,442 --> 00:20:44,742
What kind of powers?

470
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:48,846
Well, whenever I feel
   really strong emotions,
   something magical happens.

471
00:20:48,848 --> 00:20:51,849
And-and-and I never know
    what it's going to be.

472
00:20:51,851 --> 00:20:53,517
I'm trying to get
       a handle on it,

473
00:20:53,519 --> 00:20:55,386
but I'm not quite there yet.

474
00:20:55,388 --> 00:20:56,487
I'm sorry.

475
00:20:58,557 --> 00:21:01,192
There's no need
      to apologize, Elena.

476
00:21:01,194 --> 00:21:04,262
In fact, I have
    a confession of my own.

477
00:21:04,264 --> 00:21:05,696
Really?

478
00:21:05,698 --> 00:21:07,898
I don't know the first thing
  about gondolas.

479
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:10,601
Caterina is the expert,

480
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:13,237
but I felt
   like I needed to be, too,

481
00:21:13,239 --> 00:21:14,772
because I'm king.

482
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:16,307
The truth is,

483
00:21:16,309 --> 00:21:18,542
I don't know anything
    about weighing counters.

484
00:21:18,544 --> 00:21:19,810
-Counterweights.
        -Counterweights.

485
00:21:19,812 --> 00:21:21,045
-Right!
            -Right!

486
00:21:21,047 --> 00:21:23,481
So perhaps
    we should delegate this

487
